      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im seeing this weird 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout endpoint sometimes. it happens randomly during peak traffic but i cant replicate it in staging. here is the log snippet from the last crash:\n\nError: Internal Server Error\nat RequestHandler (/app/src/middleware/auth.js:42:11)\nat processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:95:5)\nUnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: Timeout error connecting to redis_cache_cluster at 10.0.2.15:6379\n{ status: 500, code: 'ECONNRESET', detail: 'connection lost' }\n\nany idea what would cause this to be intermittent?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
