    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the redis logs and they look okay, like the instance itself isnt hitting memory limits or anything. it's just these sudden drops and the connection being reset. it feels super random, like it just happens out of nowhere even when sys resources look fine. is there something else it could be besides just a basic timeout?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If Redis logs are clean, the issue might be upstream or in the network path between your API service and Redis. Check for load balancers or firewalls between the services, as they can abruptly terminate idle or saturated connections. Another possibility is that the Redis client library you are using has aggressive connection pooling or keep-alive settings that are being prematurely terminated by an intermediary device. Try temporarily increasing the connection timeouts on the client side to see if that stabilizes the endpoint.",
      "source": "target",
