      "content": "When both application and cache logs are healthy, \"random\" resets often point to intermediate network infrastructure quirks or resource exhaustion at a much lower level. Consider transient packet loss or network congestion that occurs only when traffic spikes, even if overall metrics look fine. It could also be an issue with DNS resolution timing out during connection setup under heavy load. Implementing more detailed packet-level logging or using network monitoring tools specifically during peak times might reveal these subtle delivery issues.",
